    <div class="main_page">
      <div class="page_header floating_element">
        <img src="/images/privcore_logo_black.png" alt="PrivCore Logo"/>
      </div>
      <div class="content_section floating_element">

        <div class="section_header section_header_red">
          <div id="about"></div>
          What is PrivCore?
        </div>
        <div class="content_section_text">
          <p>
                It's a automated tool which helps you with deploying IT services,
                needed in every modern <nobr>office or home.</nobr>
                It means that you can have all benefits of cloud computing, without
                sacrificing in exchange your <b>priv</b>acy or data security.
          </p><p>
                This has been achieved through a combination of several opensource technologies,
                which form a coherent whole, in order to provide basic services - the <b>core</b>.
          </p><p>
                All you need is a stable version of Debian, maybe a piece of equipment and optionally
                <nobr>(but recommended),</nobr> your own DNS domain.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="section_header">
          <div id="roundcube"></div>
            <a href="/roundcube/">Roundcube</a>
        </div>
        <div class="content_section_text">
          <p>
                Roundcube is a powerful e-mail web client. It's also integrated with XMPP
                and ownCloud.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="section_header">
          <div id="owncloud"></div>
            <a href="/owncloud/">ownCloud</a>
        </div>
        <div class="content_section_text">
          <p>
                ownCloud allows you share your files, contacts and calendar with others.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="section_header">
          <div id="owncloud"></div>
            <a href="/ldapadmin/">PhpLdapAdmin</a>
        </div>
        <div class="content_section_text">
          <p>
                Here you can do management stuff like creating new users, adding email groups and so on...
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
